And one other thing that can be as a workaround is set mp3 and mp4 formats not required for SoundManager2 initialization:
```
// somewhere in your GwtApplicationLuncher
private native void tempWorkaroundForIssue4590() /*-{
    $wnd.soundManager.audioFormats.mp3.required = false;
    $wnd.soundManager.audioFormats.mp4.required = false;
}-*/;
```
and then call that method from your overrided getConfig for example.

But that is only my assumption, I have not try this.

And yes, looks like a bug (or by design behavior) in SM2

Its another dirty way without patching soundmanager2-jsmin.js.

1. Create class CustomGwtApplication.java in package com.badlogic.gdx.backends.gwt inside your html/src folder
```
package com.badlogic.gdx.backends.gwt;

import com.badlogic.gdx.backends.gwt.preloader.Preloader;
import com.badlogic.gdx.backends.gwt.soundmanager2.SoundManager;
import com.badlogic.gdx.utils.Timer;

public abstract class CustomGwtApplication extends GwtApplication {
    @Override
    public void onModuleLoad () {
        super.onModuleLoad();

        if (!SoundManager.ok() || getPreloader() == null) {
                startPreloader();
        }
    }

    private void startPreloader() {
        final Preloader.PreloaderCallback callback = getPreloaderCallback();
        preloader = createPreloader();
        preloader.preload("assets.txt", new Preloader.PreloaderCallback() {
            @Override
            public void error (String file) {
                callback.error(file);
            }

            @Override
            public void update (Preloader.PreloaderState state) {
                callback.update(state);
                if (state.hasEnded()) {
                    getRootPanel().clear();
                    if (loadingListener != null) loadingListener.beforeSetup();
                    setupLoop();
                    if (loadingListener != null) loadingListener.afterSetup();
                }
            }
        });
    }
}
```
2. Extend your HtmlLauncher.java from newly created CustomGwtApplication

Hope that clear for you.
